  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Anne Warren Weston describes the meetings at Westford and Littleton; at the former, the audience numbered 250 and both Grimke sisters spoke; at the latter, the audience numbered 400 and only Angelina spoke. &quot;I have not heard her do so well since she has been in this part of the country.&quot; Anne rode to Pepperell on horseback alone. &quot;Tell Maria [Mrs. Maria Weston Chapman] that the cause in this part of the world is in statu quo.&quot; The Grimkes are returning (to Boston?), but will probably go directly to Brookline. Sends &quot;love to Henry, Maria, &amp; the baby.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">There is a receipt &quot;Boston 14 Aug. 1837. Rec&apos;d of H.G. Chapman, two dollars and 50/100.&quot; It is signed by Amos Lyon.</subfield>
  </datafield>
